    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Defending Napster To the Editor:</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>David Ilson letter on Aug 31 article deplores efforts to sabotage Napster's network with bogus music files; drawing</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>I was disappointed to hear that John Fix 3rd and Michael Fix (and others like them) have decided to take the law into their own hands by trying to sabotage Napster's network with bogus music files. To attempt to corrupt the music files of 22 million users with 91 files of Charlie Brown, Yosemite Sam and cuckoo sounds is both infantile and grandiose. The Fixes should realize how utterly simple it is for other Napster users to delete such files. Couldn't these guys find some other ways to fool around -- like throwing water balloons or setting off firecrackers?</p>
        <p>DAVID ILSON  Rockville Centre, N.Y.</p>
      </block>
